-- Tasnee Joint Venture Award Contracts for $1.1 Billion Plastics Facility
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2010-10-16T06:31:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/tasnee-joint-ventures-award-contracts-for-1-07-billion-plastics-plant.html
National Industrialization Co., the
Saudi Arabian petrochemical maker known as Tasnee, said two of
its units signed an agreement for the construction of a 4
billion-riyal plastics plant in Saudi Arabia.  Linde AG, the world’s second-biggest maker of industrial
gases, and South Korea’s Samsung Engineering Co. won the
engineering, procuement and construction contract for the plant,
the Riyadh-based company said in a statement on the Saudi bourse
website today.  The two Tasnee units are ventures with Sahara Petrochemical
Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
